Lower Bungee's declared cmake_minimum_required so Mixxx's source fallback
(ExternalProject_Add) can build Bungee on hosts that ship CMake older than 3.30.

Bungee upstream pins `cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.30...3.31)` as a policy
choice. The actual CMake commands Bungee uses all work in CMake 3.21+, which is
also Mixxx's global minimum. Mixxx emits a build-system warning when the host
CMake is below 3.30 to keep this clearly unsupported by Bungee maintainers.

This patch is Mixxx-specific. It is intentionally kept outside the temporary
vcpkg overlay, which mirrors microsoft/vcpkg verbatim so that overlay can be
deleted cleanly once mixxxdj/vcpkg ships the port.

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -8,7 +8,7 @@ if (BUNGEE_BUILD_SHARED_LIBRARY)
   set(CMAKE_POSITION_INDEPENDENT_CODE ON)
 endif()

-cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.30...3.31)
+cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.21)
 include(CheckCXXCompilerFlag)
 include(GNUInstallDirs)
